1. Lying.1. Concerning lying, Hoſea reckoneth it vp amongſt the ſinnes for which the Lord had a controuerſie with the Land of Iudah; and for which, he threatned that the inhabitants ſhould languiſh, and all their prouiſion (as fiſh, fleſh, and foule) ſhould be ſeized vpon by the enemie, and taken away violently as a prey Hoſ. 4.1.2.3.. They bend their tongues like bowes for lies (it's Ieremies ſpeechIer 9.3.5.7.) they will not ſpeake the truth, they haue taught their Tongue to ſpeake lies, therefore ſaith the Lord of hoſtes, behold I will melt them, and trie them (Fiſcat. Scil▪ igne afflictionis. in the fire of affliction);Puniam eos. lebita poenâ. Lyra. ad loc. I will puniſh them according to their deſeruings; how ſhall I doe for the d • ughter of my people? that is,Tantum dedecus culpae non debet dimitti ſine decore iuſtitiae. Lyra in Ier. c. 9. v. 7.
I muſt needes glorifie my iuſtice, in not ſuffering ſuch a diſgracefull ſinne as this is to eſcape Scot-free, without puniſhment. Truth is periſhed, and is cut off from their mouth Ier. 7 28.. And marke what followeth immediately;
Verſ. 29. Cut off thine hayre, oh Ieruſalem, and take vp a lamentation on high places, for the Lord hath reiected, and forſaken the generation of his wrath.

